name: Human
rec_rate_ref: Checchi thesis -- Low bound of recovery rate is 1/(stage 1 high duration + Stage2 high duration) Assuming that noone ever stays at home. Upper bound is 1/(stage 1 low duration) Assuming that everyone stays at home when infected. Should consider these alternative hypoptheses: 1) Stage 2 patients take part in transmission, 2) They don't
abundance_ref: van Dijk (1999) Via Massussi (2009). Abundance estimated +- 20%. Too much?
